vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}

direction: down

title: |md
  ## Containment Prefix Check: Why `canonical[root_len]` Matters
  `doc_root = "/var/www/html"` → `root_len = 13`
| {near: top-center}

cases: {
  style.fill: transparent
  style.stroke: transparent

  c1: "Case 1: File Inside Root" {
    style.fill: "#e8f5e9"
    style.stroke: "#388e3c"
    style.border-radius: 8

    input1: |md
      `canonical = "/var/www/html/index.html"`
    | {
      style.fill: "#c8e6c9"
      style.stroke: "#388e3c"
    }

    step1a: |md
      **Step A — strncmp**
      `strncmp("/var/www/html/index.html", "/var/www/html", 13)`
      compares first 13 bytes:
      `"/var/www/html"` == `"/var/www/html"` → **0 (match)**
    | {
      style.fill: "#dcedc8"
      style.stroke: "#558b2f"
    }

    step1b: |md
      **Step B — character-after-root**
      `canonical[13]` = `'/'`
      `'/' == '/'` → **TRUE**
    | {
      style.fill: "#dcedc8"
      style.stroke: "#558b2f"
    }

    verdict1: "PASS → serve file" {
      style.fill: "#2e7d32"
      style.font-color: white
      style.border-radius: 6
      style.bold: true
    }

    input1 -> step1a
    step1a -> step1b
    step1b -> verdict1
  }

  c2: "Case 2: Sibling Directory Attack" {
    style.fill: "#ffebee"
    style.stroke: "#c62828"
    style.border-radius: 8

    input2: |md
      `canonical = "/var/www/html2/secret.txt"`
    | {
      style.fill: "#ffcdd2"
      style.stroke: "#c62828"
    }

    step2a: |md
      **Step A — strncmp**
      `strncmp("/var/www/html2/secret.txt", "/var/www/html", 13)`
      compares first 13 bytes:
      `"/var/www/html"` == `"/var/www/html"` → **0 (match)**
      ⚠ Naive prefix check would PASS here!
    | {
      style.fill: "#ffcdd2"
      style.stroke: "#e53935"
    }

    step2b: |md
      **Step B — character-after-root**
      `canonical[13]` = `'2'`
      `'2' != '/'` AND `'2' != '\0'` → **FALSE**
    | {
      style.fill: "#ffcdd2"
      style.stroke: "#e53935"
    }

    verdict2: "FAIL → 403 Forbidden" {
      style.fill: "#b71c1c"
      style.font-color: white
      style.border-radius: 6
      style.bold: true
    }

    input2 -> step2a
    step2a -> step2b
    step2b -> verdict2
  }

  c3: "Case 3: Exact Root Directory Match" {
    style.fill: "#e8f5e9"
    style.stroke: "#388e3c"
    style.border-radius: 8

    input3: |md
      `canonical = "/var/www/html"`  *(request was `GET /`)*
    | {
      style.fill: "#c8e6c9"
      style.stroke: "#388e3c"
    }

    step3a: |md
      **Step A — strncmp**
      `strncmp("/var/www/html", "/var/www/html", 13)`
      → **0 (match)**
    | {
      style.fill: "#dcedc8"
      style.stroke: "#558b2f"
    }

    step3b: |md
      **Step B — character-after-root**
      `canonical[13]` = `'\0'` (end of string)
      `'\0' == '\0'` → **TRUE**
    | {
      style.fill: "#dcedc8"
      style.stroke: "#558b2f"
    }

    verdict3: "PASS → append index.html" {
      style.fill: "#2e7d32"
      style.font-color: white
      style.border-radius: 6
      style.bold: true
    }

    input3 -> step3a
    step3a -> step3b
    step3b -> verdict3
  }
}

code_check: |'md
**The mandatory two-condition check (Stage 4):**
c
size_t root_len = strlen(doc_root);  /* = 13 for "/var/www/html" */
if (strncmp(canonical, doc_root, root_len) != 0 ||
    (canonical[root_len] != '/' && canonical[root_len] != '\0')) {
    send_403(client_fd);   /* covers Case 2 */
    return;
}
/* Only Cases 1 and 3 reach here */


| `canonical[root_len]` | Meaning | Decision |
|---|---|---|
| `'/'` | path continues inside root dir | ✅ PASS |
| `'\0'` | canonical IS the root dir exactly | ✅ PASS → index.html |
| any other char (e.g. `'2'`) | sibling directory | ❌ FAIL → 403 |
'| {
  near: bottom-center
  style.fill: "#f3f4f6"
  style.stroke: "#6b7280"
  style.border-radius: 8
}